# Set this clone up as a running business

A clone passing the technical clone-factory gates (Gates 1-15 in
`UserRoot/.claude/rules/clone-factory-quality-gates.md`) is **code
complete**, not **launched**. To turn it into a real, payable,
indexable, observable business, walk the **master checklist**:

> **`Github/business-operations/general-sops/PROJECT-SETUP-AS-RUNNING-BUSINESS-MASTER-CHECKLIST.md`**

This is the same checklist GenFlick (`Github/genflix-movie-generator/`)
walked end-to-end — every step in the checklist points at GenFlick's
working artifacts as a copy-paste reference. There is also a Cursor
skill at `~/.cursor/skills-cursor/project-setup-as-running-business/`
with the operational summary.

## Clone-specific notes

- **Stage 3 (Vercel rootDirectory):** clones in this fleet typically
  use the repo root as the Next.js app, not `app/` — confirm before
  copying GenFlick's `rootDirectory=app` setting.
- **Stage 4 (custom domain):** every Tier-1-graduating clone gets a
  branded domain on the SymplyAI Cloudflare zone or a dedicated
  registration. Don't ship a clone publicly on a `*.vercel.app`
  default for marketing purposes.
- **Stage 7 (Stripe LIVE):** clones diverged on env naming (29/42 use
  `STRIPE_PRICE_ID_PRO` not the template's `STRIPE_PRICE_PRO`). Check
  what THIS clone's checkout route reads before setting Vercel envs
  — see `pane1776/FLEET-STRIPE-ENV-NAMING-MAP-B3-2026-04-14.md`.
- **Stage 11 (SEO):** clones using next-intl must satisfy Gates 14 +
  15 from clone-factory-quality-gates (don't exclude `/pricing` from
  the i18n matcher; standalone `/pricing/page.tsx` re-export).
- **Stage 16 (operating discipline):** the clone's `STATUS.md` must
  match its disk reality and BridgeMind board state. Stale STATUS is
  the #1 source of duplicated swarm work on this fleet.

When a coordinator dispatches "stand up clone X," the work is
**walking the master checklist for X**, not adding more features.
